Docker install
--------------

sudo yum-config-manager --add-repo https://download.docker.com/linux/centos/docker-ce.repo
yum erase podman buildah
sudo yum install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io
sudo systemctl enable --now docker && sudo systemctl status docker

The Docker daemon binds to a Unix socket instead of a TCP port. By default that Unix socket is owned by the user root and other users can only access it using sudo. The Docker daemon always runs as the root user.


Docker volume
--------------

docker build -t redis_1  -<<EOF
FROM redis
VOLUME /data
EOF

docker run --rm -d --name redis_1 redis_1
docker run --rm --name redis_1 -d --mount type=volume,source=data,destination=/data redis_1
docker stop $(docker ps -q)
docker rm -f $(docker ps -a -q)

docker volume ls
docker volume rm $(docker volume ls -q)

docker exec -it redis_1 bash
docker exec -it composetest1_proxy_1 bash


docker-compose
--------------

docker-compose build
docker-compose up -d

curl localhost:5000
curl localhost
curl flask-redis-app.test

docker compose down


docker stop $(docker ps -q); docker rm -f $(docker ps -a -q); docker volume rm $(docker volume ls -q); docker rmi -f $(docker images -q)

docker stop $(docker ps -q); docker rm -f $(docker ps -a -q); docker volume rm $(docker volume ls -q);